Examples of resazurin plates



Oyster seed loaded into a 48-well plate for resazurin testing.





Oyster seed with resazurin solution at the start of a resazurin trial. Note the dark blue color of the resazurin at the beginning of the trial.





Oyster seed with resazurin solution at the end of a 4 h resazurin trial. Note the pink color indicates fluorescence of resorufin as metabolism occurs. The variation in color indication variable metabolic responses with higher metabolism in brighter pink wells. The dark blue wells in the right hand row are blanks, required for data analysis.





Testing multiple plates with hundreds to thousands of oysters is achievable with the resazurin assay.




